## 13. demos/*.spc — P-Code Test Programs

Example: **demos/hello.spc**

```pasm
; hello.spc — Hello World for pv24a P-Code VM
;
; Expected output: Hello\n

.data msg 72, 101, 108, 108, 111, 10, 0

.proc main 0
    push msg
    call puts
    halt
.end

.proc puts 1
    loada 0
    storel 0
loop:
    loadl 0
    loadb
    dup
    jz done
    sys 1
    loadl 0
    push 1
    add
    storel 0
    jmp loop
done:
    drop
    ret 1
.end
```

**Pattern:**
- `.data` section: Byte array literal (ASCII "Hello\n")
- `.proc` sections: Named procedures with parameter count
- Stack-based calling convention
- Demonstrates: push, call, loada (load address), storel (store local), loadb (load byte), jz (jump if zero), sys (system call), ret (return)

